              "author": {
                "login": "copilot-pull-request-reviewer"
              },
              "body": "Store.Compact rewrites to a temp file and renames it over the original, but it never fsyncs the temp file before rename (and doesn’t fsync the parent dir after rename). This can lose a successfully-compacted trust.jsonl on crash/power loss, and it also diverges from docs/spec/trust-store-v1.md which explicitly calls for fsync-before-rename. Consider reusing internal/fsroot.Root.StagedWrite semantics (write+Sync+rename+best-effort dir Sync) or at least tmp.Sync() before Close()+Rename(), plus best-effort directory fsync.",
